==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trave
<hw>Trave</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Through French, fr. L.
<ets>trabs</ets>, <ets>trabis</ets>, a beam; cf. OF. <ets>tref</ets> a
beam, also F. <ets>travail</ets> a frame to confine a horse, OE.
<ets>trave</ets>, <ets>trevys</ets>, <ets>travise</ets>, It.
<ets>travaglio</ets>, F. <ets>trav⟦eacute⟧e</ets> the space between two
beams.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A crossbeam; a lay of
joists.</def> <rj><au>Maundrell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wooden frame to confine an unruly horse or ox
while shoeing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She sprung as a colt doth in the <qex>trave</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travel</ent>⟦br⟧
